{
  "stem": "4753.10",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We did go with train, and a very short way we walked.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know from where to where.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was horrible, and Auschwitz was horrible.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The snow-- the rain was falling all the time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everything was knee high mud, like in Auschwitz, where we left.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When we left Auschwitz, it was the same way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And every single day, hundreds and hundreds of inmates died.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were put into a tent because they had not enough space in the barracks anymore.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then we finally came into the barracks, but from there we were taken to work-- to Braunschweig, as I mentioned to you.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What kept me?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I don't know what-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] what keep you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, we all-- the 10 girls I am talking about-- and the rest of the group whom I was together, we never lost our dignity or human beings.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We always-- you know, the Germans wanted to make us inhuman.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wanted to take our spirit, not only our-- our energy and life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they never could, because we always tried to help each other.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] when we saw something is not right-- one thing that happened also in Braunschweig, that when we were standing in line for a piece of bread, that was a torture every night, because we were watching what size, what piece of the bread will come to us.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, as we stood in line, you can-- you could see in the basket.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And finally, I saw that an end will be my piece.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And a blockova took it out and gave it to me.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
